      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Project Overview</h2>
        <p>The Meijel Museum project is an ongoing commission to create an interactive digital experience for a touch-screen table recently installed at the museum. The experience is centred on the history of Meijel, a small village in North Limburg. The main feature is an interactive historical map of the area with a time slider, allowing visitors to scroll through centuries of history — from the earliest recorded evidence of Meijel's existence all the way to the present day. As the slider moves, buildings appear and disappear on the map according to historical records, giving visitors a tangible sense of how the village has grown and changed over time.</p>
        <p>Alongside the map, a second interactive element is planned: a magical typewriter that serves as a digital keyboard, allowing visitors to hold a conversation with an AI-powered painting of Jan Truijen — a prominent figure in Meijel's history known for his prolific letter-writing. The painting will respond in character, drawing on historical knowledge to bring the figure to life in a way that feels personal and immersive.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Client &amp; Context</h2>
        <p>The Meijel Museum purchased a touch-screen table and sought out a developer to fill it with content that would bring the village's history to life in an engaging and accessible way. The project is being developed independently, with the museum providing historical records and source material to inform the accuracy of the map and the AI character.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Current Status</h2>
        <p>The project is currently in the early planning and prototyping phase. The core concepts — the historical time-slider map and the AI typewriter — have been defined, and initial technical exploration is underway. The application will be built in Unity 3D, targeting the museum's touch-screen table hardware.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Anticipated Challenges</h2>
        <p>Building an accurate, scrollable historical map requires careful curation of historical data and a flexible data-driven system for showing and hiding buildings over time. The AI character presents its own set of challenges: crafting a persona that stays historically grounded while remaining conversational and engaging for museum visitors of all ages. Designing the physical typewriter interaction to feel intuitive and magical on a touch table — without becoming confusing or frustrating — will also require thoughtful UX work.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
